      <section eId="sec_1500_C">
        <num>1500-C</num>
        <heading>City of Buffalo parking authority</heading>
        <subsection eId="sec_1500_C__subsec_a">
          <num>(a)</num>
          <content>
            <p>The mayor of the city shall file on or before December\nthirty-first of the year in which this title shall take effect, in the\noffice of the secretary of state, a certificate signed by the mayor\nsetting forth:\n</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <subsection eId="sec_1500_C__subsec_i">
          <num>(i)</num>
          <content>
            <p>the name of the authority;\n  (ii) the names of the members of the board and their terms of office;\nand\n  (iii) the effective date of this title.\n</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <subsection eId="sec_1500_C__subsec_b">
          <num>(b)</num>
          <content>
            <p>If such certificate is not filed with the secretary of state on or\nbefore such date, then the corporate existence of the authority shall\nthereupon terminate and it shall thereupon be deemed to be and shall be\ndissolved.\n  4. The city of Buffalo parking authority shall not be authorized to\nexercise the powers, duties, and functions outlined in this article\nuntil all initial members and the initial chair are appointed.\n</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
      </section>
